What you need to know:

Agriculturalists explain why growers across the country are witnessing a rise in Tuta absoluta attack, as the pest that multiplies faster during the dry weather seemingly becomes resistant to the many pesticides in the marketJames Samo, an agriculture officer in Kisumu, says tomato farmers in nearly all the seven sub-counties of the region are reeling from the effects of the pest.The high cost of managing the pest has rendered the farming of the crop a loss-making venture as prices of the produce fluctuate from a low of Sh1,500 per crate during high supply to Sh5,000 in low season.Some agriculturalists blame the rapidly changing weather, which has seen day temperatures in some areas like Nairobi and its environs hit 29 degrees Celsius, to the increase in the pest.